---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Best Scrabble Opening Words — First Move Strategy Guide"
  description="Best first-move words in Scrabble. Why 7-letter bingos on opening = 50 bonus + DWS. Top openers: MUZJIKS, QUARTZY, JOTTERS, JUNIPER, QUILTED. Free tool."
  keywords="best scrabble opening words, first move scrabble, scrabble opening strategy, best first word scrabble, opening bingo scrabble, muzjiks scrabble, centre double word score"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Best Scrabble Opening Words — First Move Strategy Guide",
    "description": "Best first-move words in Scrabble. 7-letter bingos on opening earn 50 bonus + centre DWS. Top openers ranked with strategic analysis.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/best-scrabble-opening-words" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the best opening word in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The theoretical best opener is MUZJIKS (29 base + 50 bingo bonus = 128+ points with DWS), but it requires drawing M, U, Z, J, I, K, S on your first rack — extremely unlikely. Practical best openers are JOTTERS (64pts), JUNIPER (66pts), or QUILTED (68pts) which use common tiles with one premium letter." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does the first word in Scrabble get double word score?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes! The centre star square is a Double Word Score (DWS). Every first word automatically gets its total doubled. A 7-letter bingo opening earns: (base word score × 2) + 50 bonus. For example, JOTTERS (14 base × 2 = 28, + 50 bonus = 78 points) on your very first turn." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Should you always try for a bingo on the first move?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Not always. A bingo opening is ideal but rare (about 5-10% of starting racks can form one). If you can't bingo, prioritize: (1) using high-value tiles on the DWS, (2) keeping good rack leave (balanced vowels/consonants), (3) not opening up the board too much for your opponent. A 30-point non-bingo opener is often better than a forced 20-point play that leaves bad tiles." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Strategy</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Best Scrabble Opening Words — First Move Strategy Guide</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔍</span> Solver</a> <a href="/activities/#quiz" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎯</span> Quiz</a> <a href="/activities/#anagram" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔀</span> Anagram</a> <a href="/activities/#rack" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎲</span> Rack</a> <a href="/activities/#wotd" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">📖</span> WOTD</a> <a href="/sixty-seconds/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">⏱️</span> 60s</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Your first word sets the tone for the entire game. The centre star is a Double Word Score — every opening play gets doubled automatically. Combine that with a 7-letter bingo (50-point bonus) and your opening move can exceed 100 points. Here's how to maximize it.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">128+ pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MUZJIKS (theoretical)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">×2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Centre DWS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">+50</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Bingo Bonus</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5-10%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Bingo Probability</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why Opening Moves Matter</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🧠 The Opening Advantage</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The centre star gives every opener an automatic <span class="text-white font-medium">Double Word Score</span>. A 7-letter bingo on turn one earns: (word score × 2) + 50 bonus. Even a modest SATIRE (6pts × 2 + 50 = 62pts) crushes most mid-game plays. The first player who bingos typically wins.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Dream Openers (Theoretical Best)</h2>
      <p>These openers require improbable tile draws but represent the ceiling of what's possible on turn one.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Theoretical Best</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">MUZJIKS — 128+ Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">M=3, U=1, Z=10, J=8, I=1, K=5, S=1 = 29 × 2 (DWS) + 50 (bingo) = 108 minimum</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Russian village peasants. Uses Z (10) and J (8) together with K (5) for 29 base points. Doubled on the star to 58, plus 50 bingo bonus = 108 points. With premium square placement, it climbs higher.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 MUZJIKS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">29 base · 108+ total · Z+J+K combo · SOWPODS valid</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💎 QUARTZY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">28 base · 106+ total · Q+Z combo · Disputed validity</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Practical Bingo Openers</h2>
      <p>These 7-letter words use realistic tile combinations — one premium letter (J, Q, Z, X, K) with common tiles you'll actually draw.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📝 JOTTERS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 base × 2 + 50 = 78pts · J + common tiles</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌲 JUNIPER</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">16 base × 2 + 50 = 82pts · J + common combo</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧵 QUILTED</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">17 base × 2 + 50 = 84pts · Q+U together</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✂️JOINTER</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 base × 2 + 50 = 78pts · J + RSTLNE tiles</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚡ JESTING</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 base × 2 + 50 = 80pts · J + -ING ending</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎯 KIBBUTZ</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">24 base × 2 + 50 = 98pts · K+B+Z (rare draw)</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Opening Strategy When You Can't Bingo</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Maximize the DWS:</span> Place your highest-value letter on or near the star. JAZZ as an opener = (29 × 2) = 58 points without a bingo. High-value short words are strong openers too.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Protect your rack leave:</span> Don't dump all your best tiles. Keep a balanced leave (2-3 vowels, 3-4 consonants) for your next draw. A 24-point opener with good leave beats a 30-point opener that leaves UUOII.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Control board openness:</span> Shorter openers (4-5 letters) limit your opponent's options. Longer openers give them more hooks and parallel play opportunities. If you're behind on tile quality, keep it tight.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">5-letter sweet spot:</span> A 5-letter word through the centre star touches one letter on the DLS column. Place your premium letter there for DLS × DWS combo scoring — the multipliers stack.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">JAZZY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">66pts (×2)</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FIZZY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">58pts (×2)</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">QUICK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">40pts (×2)</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KAYAK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">30pts (×2)</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">JIFFY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">42pts (×2)</span></span>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/7-letter-words-with-z/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">7-Letter Words With Z — Complete Scrabble List</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-prefix-up/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words With Prefix UP — Scrabble Strategy Guide</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔍 Find the best opening word from your rack — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      
<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why This Matters for Your Game</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
  <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Building a strong vocabulary is the single biggest predictor of Scrabble success. Players who know <span class="text-white font-medium">more valid words score 30-50% higher</span> on average than those relying on common vocabulary alone.</p>
</div>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">30%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Score improvement</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5 min</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Daily study needed</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Free</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">No signup required</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>Whether you are preparing for tournament play or just want to beat your family at game night, the words on this page give you a competitive edge that compounds over time.</p>


<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Quick Tips</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Practice with the solver:</span> Enter your rack tiles into our free word finder to discover every valid combination. Seeing all options trains your pattern recognition over time.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Memorise in groups:</span> Rather than learning words randomly, study them by pattern — same prefix, same suffix, or same tile combination. Grouped learning is 3x more effective than isolated word lists.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Test yourself daily:</span> Pick 5 words from this page each day and try to use them in practice games. Active recall beats passive reading for long-term retention.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Explore More</p>
  <div class="grid gap-2">
    <a href="/blog/how-to-improve-at-scrabble-fast/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
      <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
      <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">How to Improve at Scrabble Fast</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/blog/scrabble-tile-bag-distribution/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
      <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
      <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Scrabble Tile Bag Distribution — All 100 Tiles</span>
    </a>
  </div>
</div>


<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🧠 Memory Technique</p>
  <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Group these words into <span class="text-white font-medium">clusters of 5</span> and learn one cluster per day. After a week, test yourself on all 35 — you will retain 80%+ using spaced repetition. Review any forgotten words the following day.</p>
</div>

<p>The most effective Scrabble study habit is short, daily sessions rather than long weekly marathons. Five minutes of focused word review every day builds permanent memory faster than an hour once a week.</p>

<div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
